cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.MA 

This paper presents a design concept and motion planning solution for a connected robotic system of systems consisting of multi-linked micro aerial vehicles. The paper focuses on the reconfigurable nature of the system and its ability to find collision-free paths in constrained and obstacle-laden environments. This work involves robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY) as it deals with the design and motion planning of a robotic system. The probabilistic strategy used in the approach involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the evaluation studies involve computer vision (cs.CV) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
